# Mobile App Standards

Native mobile app development standards (Post-MVP).

## Hard Requirements

- Do: keep mobile clients lightweight and backend-driven for business logic.
- Do: support offline behavior with clear sync strategy.
- Do not: implement complex domain logic only in mobile clients.
- Why: backend-centric logic keeps behavior consistent across platforms.

## Opinionated Defaults

- Use platform-native secure storage for auth/session tokens.
- Use native language and tooling for each platform.
- Prefer offline-first storage and background sync.
- Prefer biometric auth where product requirements demand it.

## Exceptions

- Early MVP mobile clients can defer full offline sync when explicitly scoped.
- Platform-specific deviations are acceptable when security and parity are not
  compromised.

## Acceptance Checks

- Tokens are stored securely using platform-native secure storage.
- Sync behavior handles reconnect and conflict policy explicitly.
- Mobile feature behavior matches backend API contract and permissions.

## Examples

```text
✅ GOOD - Lightweight mobile client flow
1) Read cached items from local storage for immediate render.
2) Fetch fresh items from API endpoint.
3) Merge results with conflict policy.
4) Persist merged state back to local storage.
```

```text
✅ GOOD - Secure token handling
1) Store session tokens in platform-secure storage.
2) Never log raw token values.
3) Rotate and clear tokens on logout/session expiry.
```
